y Buttons|Ruby Play Button]] award sent to him by YouTube in commemoration of his channel reaching 50 million subscribers.\n| align=\"center\" | <ref group =\"\u2021\" name=rubyplaybutton/>\n| align=\"center\" | <ref name=Cohen2016/>\n|-\n| \"Can this video get 1 million dislikes?\"\n| align=\"right\" | 24 December 2016\n| PewDiePie asks his viewers to dislike the video.\n| align=\"center\" | <ref group =\"\u2021\" name=\"1milliondislikes\">{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wx9Jv5uxfac |title=Can this video get 1 million dislikes? |date=24 December 2016 |publisher=[[YouTube]] |access-date=4 January 2019 |work=[[PewDiePie]]}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | <ref name=Weiss2016/>\n|-\n| \"STARTED A FIRE IN THE BUILDING! (Experiment Gone Wrong)\"\n| align=\"right\" | 10 January 2017\n| PewDiePie is seen slicing open a [[Furby]] with a hot knife before they incinerated the toy with small blowtorches.\n| align=\"center\" | <ref group =\"\u2021\" name=\"startedafire\">{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LjzfP-xut7Q |title=STARTED A FIRE IN THE BUILDING! (Experiment Gone Wrong) |date=10 January 2017 |publisher=[[YouTube]] |access-date=4 January 2019 |work=[[PewDiePie]]}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | <ref name=\"GuarinoPhillips2017\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2017/02/14/pewdiepie-youtubes-most-popular-star-dropped-by-disney-over-anti-semitic-jokes/ |title=Anti-Semitic jokes cause YouTube, Disney to distance themselves from PewDiePie |last=Guarino |first=Ben |last2=Phillips |first2=Kristine |date=14 February 2017 |work=[[The Washington Post]] |access-date=4 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"background:#AA98A9;\"| \"I've Discovered The Greatest Thing Online...\" \u2020\n| align=\"right\" | 11 January 2017\n| PewDiePie uses the [[Fiverr]] website.<br/>This video [[PewDiePie#Media controversies, streaming, and formatted shows (2017\u20132018)|attracted controversy and heavily negative reception from media