er=Arming Slaves in the American Revolution|publisher=Yale University Press|location=New Haven, Connecticut |pages=180\u2013208|year=2008 |isbn=978-0-300-10900-9}}\n* {{cite book |last=Rhodehamel |first=John |title=George Washington: The Wonder of the Age |publisher=Yale University Press |location=New Haven, Connecticut |year=2017 |isbn=978-0-300-21997-5 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Schwartz |first=Marie Jenkins |title=Ties That Bound: Founding First Ladies and Slaves |publisher=University of Chicago Press |location=Chicago, Illinois |year=2017 |isbn=978-0-226-14755-0 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Stathis |first=Stephen W. |title=Landmark Legislation 1774\u20132012: Major U.S. Acts and Treaties |year=2014 |publisher=CQ Press |location=Washington D.C. |isbn=978-1-4522-9229-8}}\n* {{cite book |last=Thompson |first=Mary V. |title=The Only Unavoidable Subject of Regret: George Washington, Slavery, and the Enslaved Community at Mount Vernon |publisher=University of Virginia Press |location=Charlottesville, Virginia |year=2019 |isbn=978-0-8139-4184-4 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Twohig |first=Dorothy|editor-last=Higginbotham |editor-first=Don|title=George Washington Reconsidered |chapter={{thin space}}'That Species of Property': Washington's Role in the Controversy over Slavery|chapterurl=http://gwpapers.virginia.edu/resources/articles/species/|publisher=University of Virginia Press |location=Charlottesville, Virginia|pages=114\u2013138|year=2001 |isbn=978-0-8139-2005-4}}\n* {{cite book|last=Wiencek|first=Henry|authorlink=Henry Wiencek|title=An Imperfect God: George Washington, His Slaves, and the Creation of America|year=2003|publisher=Farrar, Straus and Giroux|location=New York, New York|isbn=978-0-374-17526-9|url=https://archive.org/details/imperfectgodgeor00wien}}\n* {{cite book |last=Wood |first=Gordon S.|title=The Radicalism of the American Revolution |year=1992 |publisher=Alfred A. Knopf |location=New York, New York|isbn=978-0-679-40493-4|authorlink=Gordon S. Wood}}\n\n===Journals