 Infinite Monkey Cage]]''\n|Himself\n|Episode: \"The Science of Christmas\"\n|-\n| 2011\n|''[[The Crimson Petal and the White (miniseries)|The Crimson Petal and the White]]''\n|Henry Rackham Junior\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n|''[[Being Human (UK TV series)|Being Human]]''\n|[[List of Being Human (British TV series) characters|Mr Snow]]<ref name=Agency/>\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n|''[[Inspector George Gently]]''\n|Stephen Groves\n|Episode: \"The Lost Child\"\n|-\n| 2012\n|''[[Horrible Histories (2009 TV series)|Horrible Histories]]''\n|\n| As part of \"The League of Gentlemen\"\n|-\n| 2012\n|''[[A History of Horror|Horror Europa]]''\n| Himself\n| Documentary; also writer\n|-\n| 2014\u20132017\n|''[[Game of Thrones]]''<ref>{{cite web|last=Coming |first=Winter Is |url=http://winteriscoming.net/2013/07/sherlock-actor-mark-gatiss-cast-in-season-4/ |title=Sherlock actor Mark Gatiss cast in season 4 |publisher=Winteriscoming.net |date=17 July 2013 |accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref>\n|[[Tycho Nestoris]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://winteriscoming.net/2013/09/mark-gatisss-role-revealed/ |title=Mark Gatiss's role revealed |publisher=WinterIsComing.net |date=8 September 2013 |accessdate=12 January 2014}}</ref>\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n|''[[Mapp and Lucia (BBC TV series)|Mapp and Lucia]]''\n|Major Benjy\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n|''[[Wolf Hall (miniseries)|Wolf Hall]]''\n|[[Stephen Gardiner]]\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n|''[[Coalition (film)|Coalition]]''\n|[[Peter Mandelson]]\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Victor Frankenstein (film)|Victor Frankenstein]]''\n|Dettweiler\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[London Spy]]''\n|Rich<ref name=Agency/>\n|Episode 3\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Dad's Army (2016 film)|Dad's Army]]''\n|Colonel Theakes\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Our Kind of Traitor (film)|Our Kind of Traitor]]''\n|Billy Matlock\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Absolutely Fabulous: The Movie]]''\n|Publisher \n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Denial (2016 film)|Denial]]''\n|[[Robert Jan van Pelt]]\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Taboo (2017 TV series)|Taboo]]''\n|[[George IV of the United Kingdom|Prince Regent (later George IV)]]\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Thunderbirds Are Go (TV series)|Thunderbirds Are Go]]''\n|Professor Quentin Questa\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Gunpowder (TV series)|Gunpowder]]''\n|Robert Cecil\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Doctor Who]]''\n|The Captain\n|Episode: \"[[Twice Upon a Time (Doctor Who)|Twice Upon a Time]]\"\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Mercy]]''\n|Ronald Hall\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Christopher Robin (film)|Christopher Robin]]''\n| Giles Winslow\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Favourite (film)|The Favourite]]''\n| [[John Churchill, 1st Duke of Marlborough|Marlborough]]\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Brexit: The Uncivil War]]''\n| [[Peter Mandelson]] (voice)\n| Television film\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Good Omens (TV series)|Good Omens]]''\n| Harmony\n| Miniseries\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Dracula (2020 TV series)|Dracula]]''\n| Frank\n| Miniseries, also co-creator\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[The Father (2020 film)|The Father]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[Operation Mincemeat (film)|Operation Mincemeat]]''\n|\n| Upcoming film, Filming\n|}\n\n===Writer===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Production !! Notes !! Broadcaster\n|-\n| ''[[P.R.O.B.E.]]'' || The Zero Imperative (1994)<br>The Devil of Winterbourne (1995)<br>Unnatural Selection (1996)<br>Ghosts of Winterbourne (1996)<br>{{small|(released direct to video)}}|| N/A\n|-\n| ''[[Randall and Hopkirk (Deceased) (2000 TV series)|Randall & Hopkirk]]'' || \"Two Can Play at That Game\" (2001)<br>\"Painkillers\" (2001) || [[BBC One]]\n|-\n| ''[[The League of Gentlemen]]'' || Also co-creator<br>22 episodes (1999\u20132002, 2017)<br>(with [[Jeremy Dyson]], [[Steve Pemberton]] and [[Reece Shearsmith]]) || [[BBC Two]]\n|-\n| ''[[The League of Gentlemen's Apocalypse]]'' || Feature film (2005)<br>(with [[Jeremy Dyson]], [[Steve Pemberton]] and [[Reece Shearsmith]]) || N/A\n|-\n| ''[[Doctor Who]]'' \n| 9 episodes;\n*\"[[The Unquiet Dead]]\" (2005)\n*\"[[The Idiot's Lantern]]\" (2006)\n*\"[[Victory of the Daleks]]\" (2010)\n*\"[[Night Terrors (Doctor Who)|Night Terrors]]\" (2011)\n*\"[